Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2017; 30(47) [edited] http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=25273


Newcastle disease, Switzerland
------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 20 Nov 2017 from Mr Hans Wyss, chief veterinary officer, Schwarzenburgstrasse 161, Swiss Federal Veterinary Office, Liebefeld, Berne, Switzerland

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 17 Nov 2017
Date of confirmation of the event: 17 Nov 2017
Reason for notification: recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 15 Feb 2012
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Newcastle disease virus
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to the whole country.

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1 (CH_ND_2017_TI): Pazzalo, Lugano, Ticino
Date of start of the outbreak: 17 Nov 2017
Outbreak status: resolved on 20 Nov 2017
Epidemiological unit: farm
Total animals affected
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Birds / 6000 / 3000 / 0 / 6000 / 0
Affected population: holding with laying hens.

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Birds / 50 / 0 / 0 / 100
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive.
Epidemiological comments: In one of his two houses, the owner observed a drop-in egg production from 85 per cent to 65 per cent over 2 weeks. In this house, 90 per cent of eggs discolored and many eggs lacked a proper shell. Mortality rate was unsuspicious. The hens in the 2nd house showed no clinical signs.

Control measures
Measures applied: official disposal of carcasses, by-products and waste, stamping-out, zoning, vaccination prohibited, no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: movement control inside the country, surveillance within containment and/or protection zone, official destruction of animal products.

Diagnostic test results:
National Reference Centre for Diseases of Poultry and Rabbits, University of Zurich (national laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Birds / real-time reverse transcriptase-polymerase chain reaction (RRT-PCR) / 17 Nov 2017 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

